title: [CARBONDATA-30] Record load performance statistics
body:
## What changes were proposed in this pull request?

1)We can use a parameter "enable.data.loading.statistics" which can be configured by user to determine whether the statistics will be recorded and calculated during data loading, the default value is false.
2)We defined a dummy util, if we don't need to record the statistics, it will do nothing.

For example, we set "enable.data.loading.statistics" to "true" and run CarbonExample, the message as following:

Data load request has been received for table default.t3

```

STAGE 2.2 ->  |_maximum distinct column write dict file time: 0.053(s)

STAGE 4.1 ->  |_read csv file: 0.47(s)
STAGE 4.2 ->  |_transform to surrogate key: 0.377(s)
STAGE 4.3 ->  |_sort rows and write to temp file: 0.366(s)
```

## How was this patch tested?

Pass the exist tests.
